    "body": "Replaced by #15981 \r\n\r\nThis is my first example of creating a \"smoke\" test in C that needs to be compiled.  ~One of the existing tests for the library -- and required files -- were also explicitly copied.~\r\n\r\nCompilation options were gleaned from those generated during the normal test build process for the library, which is not ideal from a portability standpoint.\r\n\r\nTODO:\r\n\r\n- [x] Change acquisition of `cc` executable to use `which`\r\n- [x] Restructure test to prepare for a `_run_test` from #15092 \r\n~- [ ] Determine suitable way to grab `sigsegv1` from build (if becker33 doesn't do it first)~\r\n~- [ ] Replace local `_run_test` with package's version from commit bd58f41~",
